Adjust rack to top position and preheat #oven{} to 450 degrees. Bring a large #pot{} of salted water to a boil. Wash and dry produce.

Trim and halve @zucchini{1%unit} lengthwise; cut crosswise into ½-inch-thick half-moons. Peel and mince or grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}, separating whites from greens. Zest and quarter @lemon{1%unit}.

Pat @chicken breast strips{10%ounce} dry with #paper towels{} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{2%teaspoon} in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook, stirring frequently, until cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably ovenproof, pan over medium-high heat. Add zucchini; cook, stirring, until softened and lightly browned, ~{5-7%minutes}.

Add garlic and a big pinch of salt and pepper. Cook, stirring, until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes} more.

Turn off heat; transfer zucchini to a plate. Wipe out pan. Let pan cool for ~{1%minute}.

Use pan used for chicken or sausage here.

Once water is boiling, add @cheese tortelloni{9%ounce} to pot. Cook until tender and floating to the top, ~{3-4%minutes}. Reserve 1 cup pasta cooking water (2 cups for 4 servings), then drain.

While tortelloni cook, melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for zucchini over medium-high heat. Add scallion whites and cook, stirring occasionally, until just softened, ~{1%minute}.

Stir in @cheese roux concentrate{1%ounce} and ½ cup reserved pasta cooking water (1 cup for 4). Cook, stirring occasionally, until slightly thickened, ~{2-4%minutes}. Reduce heat to low.

Whisk in @cream cheese{2%tablespoon}, @Parmesan cheese{3%tablespoon}, a squeeze of lemon juice (big squeeze for 4), and a pinch of lemon zest (save remaining lemon for another use!); season with pepper.

Once sauce is finished, stir in chicken.

Stir tortelloni and zucchini into pan with sauce. If needed, stir in more reserved pasta cooking water a splash at a time until everything is coated in a creamy sauce.

Evenly sprinkle @panko breadcrumbs{1/4%cup} over tortelloni mixture. If pan isn't ovenproof, transfer mixture to a #baking dish{} now.

Bake on top rack until panko is golden brown, ~{2-4%minutes}.

Garnish tortelloni bake with scallion greens and drizzle with as much @hot sauce{1%teaspoon} as you like. Divide between plates and serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.